previous: Saudia is a member of the Arab Air Carriers Organization. The airline joined the SkyTeam airline alliance on 29 May 2012. The airline is the third largest in the Middle East in terms of revenue, behind Emirates and Qatar Airways.[4]
doc.after: When U.S. President Franklin Delano Roosevelt presented a Douglas DC-3 as a gift to King Abdul Aziz Ibn Saud in 1945, the event marked the Kingdom's gradual development of civil aviation. The nation's flag carrier, Saudia, was founded as Saudi Arabian Airlines in September 1945[5] as a fully owned government agency under the control of the Ministry of Defense, with TWA running the airline under a management contract.
